e intricate nature of hunting on the ledge in OT, or even learn how to make that assist key when they hit that all involved ridge group in DL. At least once you hit lvl 50 you had to learn how to play your class in a tough dungeon type of situation, unless of course you discover velketors and learn to join 40 other people chasing around 3 spiders and are calling that a dungeon experience) Then comes SoL and now I can see plenty of &quot;DL ridge group potential&quot; all over the place. Soon I think there will be no place for the true dungeon crawlers at all. Sure there are dungeons in SoL catering only to the &quot;larger guild groups&quot; that will be going in to take out boss mobs, or guild farming groups. But what of the 6 person pick up group that is able to take out a mob with &quot;reasonable hit pts&quot; for exp and lewts in and of itself. Another thing I have noticed is that once you are post 50 the whole &quot;pick up group&quot; situation is over. By the time you are in the post 50 game, most people have devided into Guilds and what not and are very slow to just get in any pick up groups anymore. I know everyone aboars pick up groups but if you think back to your eq beginnings, what got you soooooo hooked on the game in the first place was the Fun, and yes Risk of fighting with complete strangers.<br><br>Think of the time when, yes even &quot;YOU&quot; were a newbie, and you would group with some  people you didnt even know. Did you not have a blast? Did you not have so much fun that you went nuts on a video game and have now spent WAY more play time on it than you would have ever thought possible before getting eq? Does anyone ever think of how the game is different post 50 than it was when you were still learning the game? When you were say lvl 20, you went to your zone of choice, called out for a group, when said group was formed you had NO CLUE if it was a good group or not, but you hunted anyway and had fun. Now that you are 50, you log in spend 20 minutes just figuring out what your guild is doing for the day, if nothing you then see if any substantial amount of &quot;guildies&quot; are going to do anything that you yourself might be inclined to join in on. <br><br>I only mention all of this because my sister moved in with me recently, and I got her hooked on everquest. Last weekend, she asked me to play her character (22 ranger I had made for her) while she went to the store. Her group had broken up shortly after she left, so I went about forming another group. By the time she got back I had formed a 6 person meat grinding xp raping twinkie group. We had a psycho puller, druid,(for sow of course) Cleric, Ranger, Monk, Rogue. We were lawn mowers. I was proud of the &quot;twinkie group&quot; I had formed and figured she would be totally stoked at how fast the exp was comming in. She gets home and I turn it back over to her, and about half an hour later she degroups and loggs for a bit. I asked her how come she left the group and she tells me &quot;the group was great experience but it was boring as hell&quot; I was like why is it boring you where fighting non stop? she told me because nobody was saying a damn word, it was all about killing and there was never any talking. There were no &quot;close calls' on dying or anything we were just like a machine. <br><br>I had forgotten how fun it was to be with people I didnt know and actually goof off and have fun. Its not about what is the maximum exp you can suck out of a zone, its about meeting new people and joking and risk. Thats why I hope verant figures out a way of making an over populated deep ass dungeon viable again. Because even in the old days, I remember having a ton of fun with pick up groups (yes even though you met jerks, they at least gave you something or someone to joke about) But there was always a lot of fun in meeting new people, and the &quot;daily grind of the xp monster&quot; wasnt such a terrible thing in those days. <br><br>Anyway, I was bored and thought I would throw some of my own thoughts of late about the game at you guys to see if you beat up on me bad or not.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ualiasisudonomo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aliasi Sudonomo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New to the block</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/6/02 8:35:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=782.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ Evolution</span><hr size=1> I think you are correct in thinking that a person can now level to 50+ - 60, even - without any real dungeon experience, or close calls, or what have you... Mainly because this is exactly what happens nowadays.<br><br>I don't see an actual problem with this, however. EQ is a multiplayer game but you aren't really competing with anyone (unless you're on a Zek, natch). You can play just about any style you find fun as long as you can find one or two other folks who are willing to play in a similar fashion. Even fewer, if you can tolerate soloing.<br><br>I do agree with the general idea that if you aren't having fun in some way, you ought to quit doing it. This doesn't mean EQ has to be easy or have instant gratification, and I agree that something havign to work harder for your goal makes it *more* fun.<br><br>As for which camp I'm in... well, lets just say I'm probably more familiar with every old-world dungeon I can enter without getting squashed than 90% of the EQ population. :)<br> <p><BR><IMG SRC="http://webpages.marshall.edu/~wellma15/aliasi_sig2.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ulogixspybreak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Logix Spybreak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>AyRo IRC OP</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/6/02 9:12:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=782.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ Evolution</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> unless of course you discover velketors and learn to join 40 other people chasing around 3 spiders and are calling that a dungeon experience<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>That made me laugh out loud, sir. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ubradiouscalahan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bradious Calahan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/6/02 11:52:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=782.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ Evolution</span><hr size=1> .....The days of SK. :/<br><br>When I thought clerics were a waste of damage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uedeina.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Edeina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Board Mistress</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/6/02 2:02:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=782.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.one.se/users/chribesk/edeina.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ Evolution</span><hr size=1> Mmm, the good old days was great. I really loved LGuk. Dead side of course, the living frogs there are good so of course I would not kill them. Overcrowding was a bitvh, but that was the only real problem. And undercrowding is worse, with no pickup groups to get and so much frogs that you will get wiped out unless you have such a powerful group that the camp will get boring once you have cleared it the first time.<br><br>Before the guild politics, and before the everlasting NBG conflict. Back in guk in my days everyone rolled for everything, and that was that. Period. It might not have been the best system of distribution as such, but it was simple and most importantly free from bitching. One of the biggest drawbacks of kunark and beyond is that once a good item drops ia a pickupgroup, there will be three persons demanding different versions of need before greed, tvo demanding that everyone rolls, and one who log in fisgust after hearing these five morons yelling at each other for a few hours. I used to be that sixth person, and that's one of the main reasons why i more or less stopped doing pickupgrousp. <br><br>The main reason however, was that groups started to fall apart much more often. In Guk I spent two hours on a list while playing my twink, and once I had joined I could stay for as long as I wanted. People would leave, but they would get replaced. And people chatted and roleplayed a lot, it wasn't the mindless xp-grinding machine. In Karnor's I would spend 30 minutes searching for a group and then 10 minutes in that group untill it got trained out and lost it's camp or fell apart for other raesons. In Sebilis I would spend two hours searching for a group, and once we gotten to our camp we could not get reinforcements and not move to other groups ourselves. The group typically lasted for 30 minutes to two hours and then broke up, usually because someone had to leave or we had to evac. In guk we just took our camp back after evac, but in Sebilis there was ALWAYS some key class that would get bored as soona s things didn't go perfect and who we would not find a replacement for in time. Plus, the crypt was boring as hell! When I came back to Sebilis far later at much higher level, I learned to enjoy Chef, King and Disco. However, that was mostly with premade groups of friends and guildies. <p>Love, Edeina<br>Highelf Arch Mage of Erollisi.<br>Citizen of <a href="http://pub42.ezboard.com/bayonaero">Ayonae Ro</a>, member of <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/beternalwrath">Eternal Wrath</a>.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uhalochanter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HaloChanter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local Resident</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/6/02 2:22:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=782.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ Evolution</span><hr size=1> Sandin54.. I agree a lot!<br>I really, really miss the days such as SK, when the aviak town would be bustling with groups, when the zone would be alive with jokes and chatter. When there were 1, perhaps 2 at the max, twinks around. <br>Then when you could walk in to Cazic and grab a group and go hunt some leezards!<br>And I completely agree, pick-up groups are the way to go.<br>Don't get me wrong, I have a set group of very dear friends that I group with often that make me laugh and smile like no one else could <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  However, I'm also the type that just loves pickup groups. What is eq, if not an experience to interact and meet people? Not the same people, day in and day out, but different people! <br>Although that brings me to my other point, different people like different things. Endless people on these boards avoid pick up groups at all costs, mainly perhaps due to these 'outdoor manufactured' eq players that have begin to grow at a substansial rate. <br>Either way, I'm ready to put up with the odd moron, or loot 'whore', if it means I get to meet new people and just have a blast. There's nothing better than a social, funny, and just plain fun group.<br>Sometimes when people clearly resent pick up groups because they're 'above' it, I do pitty them. For they are missing out on one of the best experiences EQ has to offer: other players.<br>*hears Dreadnok shuddering* <p>Halo 56th Beguiler<br>Sspeed 40th Monk<br>Halo 'who broke my mezz?'<br>Tank_001 says 'me'<br>Tank_001 has been slain by Haloface.<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ukivornteleri.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kivorn Teleri</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elite Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/6/02 2:22:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=782.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ Evolution</span><hr size=1> Agreed.<br>Tho' some of us even remember when no one cared jack shit for the spires in SK <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>//Kiv <p>Kivorn the Teleri</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uconaddor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Conaddor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elite Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/6/02 5:13:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=782.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http: